                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee (Arms)/99:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-21T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 21, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 21—9:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>985. Supplementing my 984, February 20, 6 p.m., paragraph 2, I suggest
                    consideration of article 33 of the 1925 Arms Traffic Convention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
